    {
      "subcategory": "Methodology",
      "title": "Detection and exploitation techniques",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["methodology"],
      "body": "Rendered     the injection result is visible directly on the page - the simplest case.\nError-Based  the result lands in the error text (verbose errors required).\nBoolean      conditionally trigger an error → blind yes/no.\nTime-Based   conditional delay (sleep) → blind by time.\nOut-of-Band  the result goes out to your server (DNS/HTTP).\nPolyglot     one payload - the engine's reaction quickly tells you which one it is."
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Methodology",
      "title": "Where to look for SSTI",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["methodology", "recon"],
      "body": "• Generated PDFs, invoices, and emails are almost always template-based.\n• Name/greeting fields, template previews, email subjects and bodies, custom messages.\n• Any input that is later rendered back to the user.\n• Start with {{7*7}} and ${7*7}; if it evaluates, identify the engine and escalate to RCE."
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Methodology",
      "title": "Tools and resources",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["tools"],
      "body": "tplmap / SSTImap - SSTI auto-exploitation.\nHackmanit template-injection-table - an interactive polyglot table covering 44 engines.\n@0xAwali \"template-engines-injection-101\" - how to tell apart engines with identical syntax."
    },

